China will invest billions to reverse desertification by building forests around cities and other areas and upgrading irrigation.
Desertification-resistant trees (poplars, desert dates, sea buckthorn) are encouraged.
Forests and grass preserve soil by creating barriers against wind, sandstorms, and runoff.
China is building methane gas facilities as an alternative to cutting trees for fuel.
Soil erosion and degeneration threaten China’s grain security.
Black soil thickness has dropped drastically and organic content has fallen.
Recommendations for improvement include more ponds and reservoirs, leaving manure and corn stalks in fields, and growing cover crops.
China signed the UN Convention to Combat Desertification.
